# Moveswap Glitch

The **Moveswap** is one of the most famous glitches in *Dark Souls* . It allows the player to "swap" the moveset of one weapon onto another. This effectively lets you use the attack animations of a fast weapon while wielding a much heavier, more powerful one.

The most common application involves using the **Estoc** or **Rapier** as the "source" weapon. By performing the glitch, you can apply their high-speed running , rolling and backstep attacks to heavy-hitting weapons like the **Black Knight Halberd (BKH)**, **Dragon Tooth..**. This results in a massive increase in DPS (Damage Per Second), as you are hitting with the strength of a giant hammer at the speed of a thrusting sword.

It is **highly recommended to downpatch** your game to an earlier version (such as 1.01) to make the Moveswap significantly easier.

In the latest versions of *Dark Souls Remastered*, the timing window to perform the menu swap is extremely tight, making it inconsistent for many players. By downpatching, you revert to a version where the **buffer window is much more forgiving**, allowing you to perform the glitch with far greater consistency.

This Glitch was discovered by Eloise in august 2024 : [https://youtu.be/LO_cbxkc72k](https://youtu.be/LO_cbxkc72k)

